<h1>LangSci Press: Microsoft Word to <span class="latex">L<sup>a</sup>T<sub>e</sub>X</span> Conversion</h1>


The most costly part of producing books is typesetting. We accept book submissions
in <a href="http://www.libreoffice.org/">LibreOffice</a> or Microsoft Word. The submissions are
required to strictly adhere to the guidelines that will be provided soon. The references have to be
provided in a database like EndNote that allows BibTeX export.
<p>
We will use professional Word to <span class="latex">L<sup>a</sup>T<sub>e</sub>X</span> conversion software and write software for post-processing
the output of these tools. We have <!--#include virtual="sign/num_typesetters"--> typesetters who
volunteered to help with producing the final book. Typsetters who did actual work will be named on
our web-page and in the books. In addition to those who volunteered, some of the series editors and the main
organizers at the FU will take care of typesetting.



